    <p>• In­dia cap­tain Vi­rat Kohli was named the In­ter­na­tional Cricket Coun­cil’s men’s crick­eter of the decade yes­ter­day, as Aus­tralia all-rounder Ell­yse Perry swept the top women’s awards.</p>
    <p>Kohli, also the ODI (one-day in­ter­na­tional) player of the decade, lifted the 2011 World Cup and the 2013 Cham­pi­ons Tro­phy.</p>
    <p>Aus­tralian bats­man Steve Smith was crowned the best Test player.</p>


